   "source": [
    "Generator Expressions and Performance - Lecture"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5e2a00d5-d205-46b6-b511-0a302990a86a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Comprehension Syntax\n",
    "\n",
    "We already covered comprehension syntax when we studied list comprehensions\n",
    "\n",
    "l = [i ** 2 for i in range(5)]\n",
    "\n",
    "As well as more complicated syntax:\n",
    "- if statements\n",
    "- multiple nested loops\n",
    "- nested comprehensions\n",
    "\n",
    "[(i,j)\n",
    " for i in range(1, 6) if i%2==0\n",
    " for j in range(1, 6) if j%3==0]\n",
    "\n",
    "[[i*j for j in range(5)] for i in range(5)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "cc1e066c-daac-4ac7-988b-14985aec6a16",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Generator Expressions\n",
    "\n",
    "Generator expressions use the same comprehension syntax -> including nesting, if\n",
    "but instead [] we use ()\n",
    "\n",
    "[i**2 for i in range(5)]\n",
    "a list is returned\n",
    "evaluation is eager\n",
    "has local scope\n",
    "can access nonlocal and global scopes\n",
    "iterable\n",
    "\n",
    "(i**2 for i in range(5))\n",
    "a generator is returned\n",
    "evaluation is lazy\n",
    "has local scope\n",
    "can access nonlocal and global scopes\n",
    "iterator (generator)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3241c730-cec9-4fb8-b43b-20365c0deb13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Resource Utilization\n",
    "\n",
    "List comprehensions are eager\n",
    "All objects are created right away\n",
    "-> takes longer to create/return the list\n",
    "-> iteration is faster (objects already created)\n",
    "-> entire collections is loaded into memory\n",
    "\n",
    "Generators are lazy\n",
    "Object creation is delayed until requested by next()\n",
    "-> generator is created/returned immediately (nothing to calculate) \n",
    "-> iteration is slower (objects need to be created)\n",
    "-> only a single item is loaded at a time\n",
    "\n",
    "If you iterate through all elements -> time performance is about the same\n",
    "If you do not iterate through all the elements -> generator is more efficient\n",
    "In general, generators tend to have less memory overhead\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
